MapPlot class plots the graph on the UI by inheriting from the JPanel class takes the coordinates given in the file and the object from MinMaxScaler to properly plot inside the UI has a constructor which sets the coordinates on the UI according to user's screen
MinMaxScaler
MinMaxScaler class scales the coordinates between some boundaries so that the graph can be plotted in the correct place in the GraphPlot class makes attributes for min, max for both x and y coordinates which will be used later on in the GraphPlot has a constructor which makes the boundary of 0 and 1 and scales the points into these boundaries
